               <floruit notBefore="1597" notAfter="1650">
                  <persName ref="PRS2614BeelaK">Bǝʿǝla Krǝstos</persName>
                  was an aristocrat  from <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName>, 
                  was the governor of <placeName ref="LOC6167Walaqa">Walaqā</placeName> 
                  at the turn of the 17th century, 
                  during the reign of <persName ref="PRS10198Yaeqob">Yāʿqob</persName>.
                  He was loyal to the monarch and devoted
                  to  
                  <persName ref="PRS2226Atnatewo">
                     <roleName type="title">rās</roleName> ʾAtnātewos</persName> who was his relative and superior. 
                  After the death of <persName ref="PRS10198Yaeqob">Yāʿqob</persName>, 
                  he continued to serve loyally 
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Susǝnyos</persName>. 
                  In <date>1629</date>, he became the governor of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2639Dekana">Dǝḵānā</placeName>, 
                  then <placeName ref="LOC2488Damot">Dāmot</placeName> in <date>1632</date>. 
                  Later, <persName ref="PRS2614BeelaK">Bǝʿǝla Krǝstos</persName> served 
                
                  <persName ref="PRS4015Fasilada">  
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Fāsiladas</persName> as well until his death. </floruit>
               <death when="1650" cert="medium"/>
                  
                  
